The ANC's National Executive Committee is meeting this weekend as the knives are out between Jacob Zuma and Cyril Ramaphosa. Anlie explores this further with political analyst Karima Brown. Courtesy#DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - ANC president Cyril Ramaphosa wants to appear before the party's integrity committee. This to clear his name over corruption allegations levelled against him by some of his comrades. READ: Zuma's letter expected to be on the agenda at ANC NEC meeting Ramaphosa told the ANC National Executive Committee that he will write to the committee to explain the funding of the CR17 campaign, that secured him the ANC presidency in 2017. Political analyst Karima Brown believes that Ramaphosa's decision to appear before party's integrity committee will likely put ANC Secretary-General Ace Magashule in a tight corner. ANC president Cyril Ramaphosa wants to appear before the party's integrity committee This to clear his name over corruption allegations levelled against him by some of his comrades. Courtesy#DStv403